    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-04-22T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-04-22T18:00:00-05:00" n="459"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856d.6363/74: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-22T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. Your telegram 45 of April 18, 6 p.m. See note under date of November 2,
                        1920,<note n="14" xml:id="d459fn14">
                        <ref target="frus1920v03#pg_284">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1920, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 284</ref>.</note> especially paragraph
                    number eight, enclosed with instruction 97, November 11, 1920.<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d459fn15">
                        <ref target="frus1920v03#pg_286">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>., p. 286</ref>.</note> Much publicity is
                    being given to the subject of the Djambi oil concession. If the Senate publishes
                        report<note n="16" xml:id="d459fn16">See S. Doc. 11, 67th Cong., 1st
                        sess.</note> referred to in Department’s telegram 2, January 18, 6
                        p.m.,<note n="17" xml:id="d459fn17">Not printed.</note> further public
                    notice will be drawn to this concession. With this publicity, if American
                    interests are practically completely excluded from the Dutch oil business, an
                    unfavorable impression would be created and the situation would be discouraging
                    to Americans considering participation in other lines of Dutch industry.</p>
                <p>With respect to its future attitude regarding American investments in the
                    Netherland East Indies, the Department does not desire to commit itself to the
                    extent suggested in your telegram under reference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
